<item>
            <title>[LU-11750] lsvcgssd crash with latest krb5-libs</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-11750</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When preparing RFP for customer DDBJ (DNA Bank of Japan), we noticed Lustre does not support latest krb5 version, as provided in CentOS 7.&lt;br/&gt;
Indeed, from krb5-libs version 1.15, lsvcgssd daemon crashes when invoked for Kerberos credentials handling, thus preventing use of any Kerberos flavor with Lustre.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
